# 🎯 Sport & Health Marketplace - Core Rules

## Product Philosophy

**Always prioritize:**
- **MVP-first thinking**: Simple solutions over complex ones
- **Clean UX**: Mobile-friendly, clear hierarchy
- **Role separation**: Athlete, Coach, Admin (never break this)

**Never:**
- Over-engineer or add enterprise patterns prematurely
- Add features not explicitly requested
- Use hardcoded color values (hex) instead of design tokens

---

## Stack & Architecture

- **Framework**: Next.js App Router
- **Backend**: Supabase (Auth, DB, RLS)
- **Dependencies**: Always use **UV** library for Python dependencies
- **Auth**: Server-side `getCurrentUserWithProfile()`, `requireRole()`
- **Security**: RLS policies on all tables

---

## Design System (CRITICAL)

**Always use design tokens from `tailwind.config.ts`:**

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD - Use palette tokens
className="bg-palette-forest-dark text-white"
className="border-palette-olive hover:bg-palette-sage"

// ❌ BAD - Hardcoded colors
className="bg-[#2c3e2e] text-white"
```

**Color palette:**
- `palette-forest-dark`, `palette-forest-darker` - Primary actions
- `palette-olive`, `palette-sage` - Secondary, backgrounds
- `palette-gold`, `palette-amber` - Highlights
- `palette-strava` - Strava integration
- `palette-danger` - Errors, destructive actions

**Component library:**
- Use existing components: `Button`, `Input`, `Textarea`, `Badge`, `SportTileSelectable`
- Check `docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md` before creating new components

---

## Code Conventions

### File Structure
```
/app/dashboard     → Main app (role-based views)
/app/admin         → Admin-only pages
/components        → Shared components
/utils             → Auth, Supabase clients
```

### TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled
- No `any` types - use proper typing
- Server actions in separate files

### React/Next.js
- Server Components by default
- Client Components only when needed (`'use client'`)
- Colocate related code

---

## Security

**Every database operation MUST respect:**
1. RLS policies (Row Level Security)
2. Role-based access (athlete/coach/admin)
3. Server-side validation

---

## User Roles

| Role | Can | Cannot |
|------|-----|--------|
| **Athlete** | View workouts, send requests, chat, rate coach | Create workouts for others |
| **Coach** | Create offers, manage athletes, create workouts | Access other coaches' data |
| **Admin** | Manage members, view all data | Break RLS policies |

---

## Performance

- Minimize client-side JavaScript
- Use Supabase queries efficiently (select only needed fields)
- Avoid N+1 queries

